defs.docs: A library for acquiring a backtrace at runtime

defs.name: trace
defs.docs:
Inspects the current call-stack, passing all active frames into the closure
 provided to calculate a stack trace.

defs.name: trace_unsynchronized
defs.docs: Same as `trace`, only unsafe as it's unsynchronized.

defs.name: Frame
defs.docs:
A trait representing one frame of a backtrace, yielded to the `trace`
 function of this crate.

defs.name: ip
defs.docs: Returns the current instruction pointer of this frame.

defs.name: symbol_address
defs.docs: Returns the starting symbol address of the frame of this function.

defs.name: resolve
defs.docs:
Resolve an address to a symbol, passing the symbol to the specified
 closure.

defs.name: resolve_frame
defs.docs:
Resolve a previously capture frame to a symbol, passing the symbol to the
 specified closure.

defs.name: resolve_unsynchronized
defs.docs: Same as `resolve`, only unsafe as it's unsynchronized.

defs.name: resolve_frame_unsynchronized
defs.docs: Same as `resolve_frame`, only unsafe as it's unsynchronized.

defs.name: Symbol
defs.docs: A trait representing the resolution of a symbol in a file.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Returns the name of this function.

defs.name: addr
defs.docs: Returns the starting address of this function.

defs.name: filename_raw
defs.docs:
Returns the raw filename as a slice. This is mainly useful for `no_std`
 environments.

defs.name: lineno
defs.docs: Returns the line number for where this symbol is currently executing.

defs.name: filename
defs.docs: Returns the file name where this function was defined.

defs.name: SymbolName
defs.docs:
A wrapper around a symbol name to provide ergonomic accessors to the
 demangled name, the raw bytes, the raw string, etc.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new symbol name from the raw underlying bytes.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs: Returns the raw (mangled) symbol name as a `str` if the symbol is valid utf-8.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: Returns the raw symbol name as a list of bytes

defs.name: clear_symbol_cache
defs.docs: Attempt to reclaim that cached memory used to symbolicate addresses.

defs.name: Bytes
defs.docs: A slice, typically provided on Unix platforms.

defs.name: Wide
defs.docs: Wide strings typically from Windows.

defs.name: BytesOrWideString
defs.docs:
A platform independent representation of a string. When working with `std`
 enabled it is recommended to the convenience methods for providing
 conversions to `std` types.

defs.name: to_str_lossy
defs.docs:
Lossy converts to a `Cow<str>`, will allocate if `Bytes` is not valid
 UTF-8 or if `BytesOrWideString` is `Wide`.

defs.name: into_path_buf
defs.docs: Provides a `Path` representation of `BytesOrWideString`.

defs.name: BacktraceFmt
defs.docs: A formatter for backtraces.

defs.name: Short
defs.docs: Prints a terser backtrace which ideally only contains relevant information

defs.name: Full
defs.docs: Prints a backtrace that contains all possible information

defs.name: PrintFmt
defs.docs: The styles of printing that we can print

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a new `BacktraceFmt` which will write output to the provided
 `fmt`.

defs.name: add_context
defs.docs: Prints a preamble for the backtrace about to be printed.

defs.name: frame
defs.docs: Adds a frame to the backtrace output.

defs.name: finish
defs.docs: Completes the backtrace output.

defs.name: BacktraceFrameFmt
defs.docs: A formatter for just one frame of a backtrace.

defs.name: backtrace_frame
defs.docs: Prints a `BacktraceFrame` with this frame formatter.

defs.name: backtrace_symbol
defs.docs: Prints a `BacktraceSymbol` within a `BacktraceFrame`.

defs.name: symbol
defs.docs:
Prints a raw traced `Frame` and `Symbol`, typically from within the raw
 callbacks of this crate.

defs.name: print_raw
defs.value: fn (&mut self, frame_ip: *mut c_void, symbol_name: Option<crate::SymbolName>, filename: Option<BytesOrWideString>, lineno: Option<u32>) -> fmt::Result
defs.docs: Adds a raw frame to the backtrace output.

defs.name: Backtrace
defs.docs: Representation of an owned and self-contained backtrace.

defs.name: BacktraceFrame
defs.docs: Captured version of a frame in a backtrace.

defs.name: BacktraceSymbol
defs.docs: Captured version of a symbol in a backtrace.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Captures a backtrace at the callsite of this function, returning an
 owned representation.

defs.name: new_unresolved
defs.docs:
Similar to `new` except that this does not resolve any symbols, this
 simply captures the backtrace as a list of addresses.

defs.name: frames
defs.docs: Returns the frames from when this backtrace was captured.

defs.name: resolve
defs.docs:
If this backtrace was created from `new_unresolved` then this function
 will resolve all addresses in the backtrace to their symbolic names.

defs.name: ip
defs.docs: Same as `Frame::ip`

defs.name: symbol_address
defs.docs: Same as `Frame::symbol_address`

defs.name: symbols
defs.docs: Returns the list of symbols that this frame corresponds to.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Same as `Symbol::name`

defs.name: addr
defs.docs: Same as `Symbol::addr`

defs.name: filename
defs.docs: Same as `Symbol::filename`

defs.name: lineno
defs.docs: Same as `Symbol::lineno`
